[1] China: National Health Commission 5 May 2020; 82 883 total cases, 4633 deaths
Date: Tue 5 May 2020
Source: China National Health Commission [in Chinese, machine trans., edited]
http://www.nhc.gov.cn/xcs/yqtb/202005/8dad5d44ced34a45ae86b3acf0bbef3c.shtml


From 0 to 24:00 on [5 May 2020], 31 provinces (autonomous regions and municipalities) and the Xinjiang Production and Construction Corps reported 2 newly confirmed cases (in Shaanxi), both of which were imported; no new deaths were reported; 2 new suspected cases (in Shanghai), both imported from abroad.

On the same day [5 May 2020], 58 new cases recovered and were discharged, 517 close contacts were released from medical observation, and the condition of 3 severe cases improved.

There are 278 confirmed cases imported overseas (including 5 severe cases) and 5 suspected cases. A total of 1678 cases were confirmed, 1400 cases recovered and were discharged, and no deaths [among this group] were reported.

As of 24:00 on [5 May 2020], according to the reports of 31 provinces (autonomous regions and municipalities) and the Xinjiang Production and Construction Corps, there were 339 confirmed cases (including 26 severe cases), a total of 77 911 cases were discharged, and 4633 deaths were recorded. A total of 82 883 confirmed cases were reported, and 5 suspected cases are currently [being monitored]. A total of 735 577 close contacts have been traced, and 6973 close contacts were still under medical observation.

31 provinces (autonomous regions, municipalities directly under the Central Government) and Xinjiang Production and Construction Corps reported 20 new cases of asymptomatic infection (3 overseas imports); no conversion to confirmed cases; 64 cases under medical observation were discharged (9 cases imported from abroad); 903 cases of asymptomatic infection (88 cases imported from abroad) are still under medical observation.

A total of 1523 confirmed cases were reported from Hong Kong, Macau, and Taiwan. Among them, 1040 cases in the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region (920 cases discharged, 4 deaths), 45 cases in the Macau Special Administrative Region (39 cases discharged), and 438 cases in Taiwan (334 cases discharged, 6 deaths).

