[According to the report above, a total of 82 883 cases of confirmed COVID-19 have now been reported from mainland China, including 4633 deaths, representing an increase of 2 cases in the 24 hours since yesterday's (4 May 2020) report. The newly reported cases are in Shaanxi and both are imported cases. In Hong Kong, where numbers of newly confirmed cases had been reported daily, there were no newly confirmed cases reported in the past 24 hours. And Macau has reported no newly confirmed cases. A total of 1678 imported cases have been identified.

As best as I can tell from the machine-translated report above, there were 20 newly confirmed infections in asymptomatic people in the past 24 hours, there were 3 imported cases. There were no cases of conversion from asymptomatic to symptomatic in the past 24 hours. The total number of asymptomatic individuals currently under observation (and isolation) is 903, and 88 of these are importations from abroad. It would be helpful to know what proportion of asymptomatic infected individuals went on to be symptomatic to start developing projections of actual infection rates and adjust reported case fatality ratios accordingly. It is apparent that there is most likely thorough contact tracing and testing to explain the daily reports of asymptomatic infections in addition to the screening of individuals arriving from overseas.

As reported on 24 Mar 2020, China ended the lockdown in Hubei and elsewhere, and ended it in Wuhan on 7 Apr 2020. There is much caution and skepticism in the media over the reality of the zero case reports. The world is watching carefully to see whether this is safe timing. While there had been locally transmitted cases in both Guangdong and Heilongjiang that are of concern, there have been no reported cases from Guangdong since 28 Apr 2020 and no reports of cases in Heilongjiang since 30 Apr 2020. In recent days the main concern are importations.

A map of China showing provinces can be seen at https://sacu.org/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/provmap.png and a HealthMap/ProMED-mail map is available at https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=7304317,155. - Mod.MPP]

