From the English language summary for 5 May 2020
https://www.cdc.go.kr/board/board.es?mid=&bid=0030

- All the confirmed cases are imported cases, and there are no community transmitted cases reported today [5 May 2020]. Imported cases were from Europe (1), the Americas(1), and other (Kuwait, 1).

- In the recent 'COVID-19 national threat awareness survey' conducted targeting 1000 adults nationwide, results have shown that the people trust and take considerable interest regarding the government's daily press briefing twice a day.
* source: 4th survey on national threat awareness on COVID-19 (Seoul National University Public Health Graduate School prof Myungsoon Yoo)
-- 79.3% answered that they are 'attentive' to the government's press briefing conducted by KCDC and Central Disaster and Safety Countermeasure Headquarters, 77.4% answered that it was 'useful,' and 75.3% answered that they 'trust' the press briefings.

- KCDC stated that it will continue its efforts in providing rapid, transparent, and scientific evidenced-based information in order to assist the nation's accurate risk assessment as well as minimizing the damage by COVID-19 outbreak.
-- KCDC also shared its deepest gratitude to journalists and media who are recording Korea's COVID-19 response measures and helping the nation to overcome the crisis through everyday articles and news reports.

