[In the past 24 hours, the tally of confirmed cases of COVID-19 in South Korea has increased by 2 cases and 1 death compared with yesterday's 24-hour period (4 to 5 May 2020) when there were 3 newly confirmed cases and 2 deaths. A total of 10 806 confirmed cases and 255 deaths were reported today (5 May 2020), up from 10 804 cases and 254 deaths yesterday (4 May 2020). The daily newly confirmed case count has been at or below 100 for 34 consecutive days and below 50 for 27 consecutive days. None of the 17 regions reported newly confirmed cases; all of the 2 newly confirmed cases were imported cases, both in quarantine. This is now day 1 with no newly confirmed cases outside of quarantine, and day 2 of no locally transmitted cases. While it is too soon to conclude that transmission has been interrupted, the move to social distancing helped impact local transmission, so during the past 2 weeks, 73.6% of newly confirmed cases were importation related (as per the pie chart in the 5 May 2020 English language report). As they move to the next phase "Distancing in Daily Life," all eyes will be on the country to see if they can maintain the level of control they have had.

A map of South Korea showing provinces can be seen at https://www.nationsonline.org/oneworld/map/korea-south-administrative-map.htm and a HealthMap/ProMED-mail map at https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=7304317,195. - Mod.MPP]

